describe('Foreign Tax Credit (FTC)', () => {
  it('calculates FTC when US tax < Canada tax on US portion', () => {
    const result = calculateForeignTaxCredit(
      7000,  // US tax paid
      50000, // US-sourced income
      100000, // Total income
      20600  // Canada tax on $100k (approx $14,350 fed + $6,250 BC)
    );
    expect(result.ftcAmount).toBe(7000); // Full US tax credited
    expect(result.remainingCanadaTax).toBeCloseTo(13600, 0);
    expect(result.excessUSCredit).toBe(0);
  });

  it('calculates FTC when US tax > Canada tax on US portion (excess lost)', () => {
    const result = calculateForeignTaxCredit(
      12000, // High US tax paid (maybe high-tax state)
      50000, // US-sourced income
      100000, // Total income
      20600  // Canada tax
    );
    const canadaTaxOnUSPortion = 20600 * 0.5; // $10,300
    expect(result.ftcAmount).toBeCloseTo(10300, 0); // Limited to Canada's share
    expect(result.remainingCanadaTax).toBeCloseTo(10300, 0);
    expect(result.excessUSCredit).toBeCloseTo(1700, 0); // $12k - $10.3k
  });

  it('handles 100% US-sourced income', () => {
    const result = calculateForeignTaxCredit(
      18000,
      100000,
      100000,
      20600
    );
    expect(result.ftcAmount).toBe(18000); // Full US tax credited
    expect(result.remainingCanadaTax).toBeCloseTo(2600, 0);
  });

  it('handles zero US-sourced income', () => {
    const result = calculateForeignTaxCredit(
      5000,
      0,
      100000,
      20600
    );
    expect(result.ftcAmount).toBe(0);
    expect(result.remainingCanadaTax).toBe(20600);
    expect(result.excessUSCredit).toBe(5000);
  });
});
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. Run `npm test` → all 13 tests pass (3 federal, 3 provincial, 4 FTC, 3 edge cases)
2. $100k CAD income, BC: Federal $14,300-$14,400, provincial $6,200-$6,300, total $20,500-$20,700, effective ~20.6%
3. $100k CAD, ON: Federal $14,300-$14,400, provincial $6,850-$6,950, total $21,150-$21,350
4. $100k CAD, AB: Federal $14,300-$14,400, provincial $7,800-$7,850 (flat 10% on taxable), total $22,100-$22,250
5. FTC scenario: $100k total, $50k US-sourced, $7k US tax, $20.6k Canada tax → FTC $7k (full credit), net Canada tax $13.6k
6. FTC excess scenario: $100k total, $50k US-sourced, $12k US tax, $20.6k Canada tax → FTC capped at $10.3k (Canada's 50% share), excess $1.7k lost, net Canada tax $10.3k
7. Edge cases: Income at BPA = $0 tax, zero US-sourced income = no FTC

